      <subsection name="Relational Database">

      <blockquote>  
        <table>
         <tr>
          <td>Overall</td>
   <td>
     <span class='admin-48 icon-48'/>
   </td>
      
   <td>
          Hippo CMS uses a relational database for it's datastorage. By default 
          <a href='http://db.apache.org/derby/'>Apache Derby</a> &gt; 10.0
          is embedded and configured and runs "out of the box". 
          Hippo CMS can easily be configured to use an other relational database. 
          Possibilities are e.g.:
        <ul>
          <li>MySQL 5.0 and 5.1</li>
          <li>PosgreSQL 8.0 or newer</li>
          <li>Oracle 9.2, 10 and 11</li>
          <li>MS SQLServer 2000 or newer</li>
        </ul>         
   </td>
   </tr>
 
         <tr>
          <td>
           Tested
          </td>
   <td>
     <span class='tested-48 icon-48'/>
   </td>
          <td>Hippo ECM is contineously tested with
           <ul>
            <li> 
              <a href="http://db.apache.org/derby/">Apache Derby</a>               and 
        </li>
            <li>
              <a href="http://www.mysql.com">MySQL</a>.
        </li>
       </ul>
          </td>
    </tr>

    </table>
